## ACCESSIBILITY

### Every interactive element needs an accessible name
Icon-only buttons must have `aria-label` (or `title` as a fallback — prefer `aria-label`):

```tsx
// ❌
<button onClick={ close }>×</button>

// ✅
<button onClick={ close } aria-label="Close">×</button>
```

### Semantic HTML first
Use the right element before reaching for ARIA:

| Situation | Element |
|---|---|
| Clickable action | `<button>` |
| Navigation links | `<nav>` + `<a>` |
| Page landmark | `<main>`, `<header>`, `<footer>`, `<aside>` |
| Grouping content | `<section>` (with heading), `<article>` |
| Overlay dialog | `<dialog>` or `role="dialog"` + `aria-modal="true"` |

Never attach `onClick` to a `<div>` or `<span>` without also adding `role="button"`, `tabIndex={0}`, and keyboard handlers (`onKeyDown`).

### Focus management
- Modals must trap focus inside while open. On close, return focus to the trigger element.
- Use `autoFocus` only on the first interactive element inside a newly opened dialog/modal.
- Never remove `:focus-visible` styles without providing an equivalent visible focus indicator.

### Keyboard navigation
Every action reachable by mouse must be reachable by keyboard. Common gaps:
- Drag-and-drop boards: provide a keyboard-accessible move action (arrow keys or explicit move button)
- Custom dropdown menus: implement arrow-key navigation and `Escape` to close
- Modal dialogs: `Escape` to close

