## WARE SANDBOX RULES

### No WordPress dependencies
Wares run in a sandboxed iframe. There is no `wp` global, no `@wordpress/*` packages, and no WP REST nonce. Never import or call:
- `wp.apiFetch`, `@wordpress/api-fetch`
- `window.wp`, `window.wpApiSettings`
- Any `@wordpress/*` package

### No cross-frame access
`window.parent`, `window.top`, and `window.frameElement` are blocked by the iframe sandbox and CSP. Do not attempt cross-frame communication unless specifically implementing the `@bazaar/client` postMessage protocol.

### No external CDN resources
CSP blocks third-party origins. Bundle everything:
- No Google Fonts `@import` or `<link>` — use the system font stack
- No CDN script tags — bundle all dependencies with Vite
- No remote images in CSS — use bundled SVGs or data URIs

System font stack:
```css
font-family: -apple-system, BlinkMacSystemFont, 'Segoe UI', system-ui, sans-serif;
```

### Persistence
| Use case | Approach |
|---|---|
| Ware-local data | `localStorage` with key `bazaar-{ware-slug}-v{n}` |
| Cross-ware shared data | `@bazaar/client` SDK |
| Schema migrations | Bump the version suffix in the key |

Always wrap `localStorage` reads in try/catch — storage can be full or blocked:

```ts
export function loadState(): AppState {
    try {
        const raw = localStorage.getItem( 'bazaar-myware-v1' );
        if ( raw ) return JSON.parse( raw ) as AppState;
    } catch {
        // corrupt data or storage unavailable — fall through to default
    }
    return structuredClone( DEFAULT_STATE );
}
```

